WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.000
How do you feel when you hear these words?
当你听到这些话时，你感觉如何？

00:00:03.000 --> 00:00:05.000
Let's go around and introduce ourselves.
让我们轮流自我介绍一下。

00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:09.000
Does that make you want a panic, run, or even hide?
这会让你感到恐慌、想逃跑、甚至躲起来吗？

00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:11.000
Well, you won't any more after you watch this video.
看完这个视频，你就再也不会了。

00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:15.000
Because I'm going to give you a super simple three-step formula
因为我要给你一个超级简单的三步公式

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:19.000
to introduce yourself professionally with ease and confidence
让你轻松自信地进行职业自我介绍

00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:21.000
every single time.
每一次都是如此。

00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:23.000
Alright, so this formula has three steps.
好的，这个公式有三个步骤。

00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:26.000
First, you're going to say something about the present.
首先，你要说一些关于现在的事情。

00:00:26.000 --> 00:00:30.000
Then you're going to mention something briefly about the past.
然后简要地提一下过去。

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:33.000
And then you're going to end your introduction with something about the future.
最后用关于未来的内容结束你的自我介绍。

00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:36.000
So, present, past, future.
就是现在、过去、未来。

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:40.000
And the idea here is to keep your introduction short and sweet.
关键是要让你的自我介绍简短而美好。

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:43.000
It should be no longer than about 20 seconds.
不应超过大约20秒。

00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:45.000
Step one, the present.
第一步，现在。

00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:50.000
So, to start your introduction, you're going to say who you are and what you do now.
开始你的自我介绍时，要说你是谁以及你现在做什么。

00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:53.000
So, for example, if it's a more formal situation
比如说，如果是比较正式的场合

00:00:53.000 --> 00:00:56.000
and you're in a room with people from other companies,
你和来自其他公司的人在一个房间里

00:00:56.000 --> 00:00:58.000
you could say something like,
你可以这样说

00:00:58.000 --> 00:00:59.000
Hello, everyone.
大家好。

00:00:59.000 --> 00:01:00.000
I'm Jennifer Smith.
我是Jennifer Smith。

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:03.000
I'm a software development manager at ABC Company,
我是ABC公司的软件开发经理

00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:06.000
where I'm responsible for the building of new systems
负责构建新系统

00:01:06.000 --> 00:01:08.000
and prevention of issues.
和问题预防。

00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:10.000
If it's a more informal situation,
如果是比较非正式的场合

00:01:10.000 --> 00:01:12.000
stay, you're just starting a new job
比如你刚开始一份新工作

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:15.000
and you're introducing yourself to your new co-workers.
你在向新同事介绍自己。

00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:17.000
You could say something like,
你可以这样说

00:01:17.000 --> 00:01:18.000
Hi, all.
嗨，大家好。

00:01:18.000 --> 00:01:19.000
I'm Joe.
我是Joe。

00:01:19.000 --> 00:01:21.000
I'm part of the North America Marketing team,
我是北美市场团队的成员

00:01:21.000 --> 00:01:24.000
and I'll be looking after generation of new leads.
负责开发新潜在客户。

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:28.000
Now, here, just mention your primary responsibility,
在这里，只提你的主要职责

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:31.000
not every single task that you do in your job.
而不是你工作中的每一项任务。

00:01:31.000 --> 00:01:34.000
And especially if you're working for an American company,
尤其是如果你在一家美国公司工作

00:01:34.000 --> 00:01:36.000
don't mention any personal details,
不要提及任何个人信息

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:38.000
like how old you are,
比如你的年龄

00:01:38.000 --> 00:01:40.000
whether you're married or single,
你结婚了还是单身

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:43.000
your hobbies just keep it to the professional side.
你的爱好，只局限于职业方面。

00:01:43.000 --> 00:01:46.000
Quick question before we move on.
在继续之前，快速提问。

00:01:46.000 --> 00:01:49.000
Do you have to speak English in your current job right now?
你目前的工作中需要说英语吗？

00:01:49.000 --> 00:01:52.000
Tell me in the comments, either yes or no.
在评论中告诉我，是或不是。

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:56.000
Alright, moving on to step two of the past.
好的，现在进入第二步，过去。

00:01:56.000 --> 00:02:00.000
So now is the time where you're going to want to mention something brief
现在是时候简要提一下

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:02.000
and relevant about your background.
关于你背景中相关的事情。

00:02:02.000 --> 00:02:06.000
Something that's going to help people get to know you just a little bit more
一些能帮助人们多了解你一点的事情

00:02:06.000 --> 00:02:08.000
and also establishes your credibility.
同时也能建立你的可信度。

00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:13.000
So think about some things that are relevant to the people you're talking to.
想想那些与你的谈话对象相关的事情。

00:02:13.000 --> 00:02:18.000
Things like past projects, companies you've worked for other achievements
比如过去的项目、你工作过的公司、其他成就

00:02:18.000 --> 00:02:21.000
and just pick one of those things to highlight.
从中选一个来突出说明。

00:02:21.000 --> 00:02:23.000
So one example might be,
一个例子可能是

00:02:23.000 --> 00:02:25.000
my background is in computer science.
我的背景是计算机科学。

00:02:25.000 --> 00:02:27.000
Before taking on this role,
在担任这个职位之前

00:02:27.000 --> 00:02:30.000
I work with big data together insights for our clients
我利用大数据为客户整合洞察

00:02:30.000 --> 00:02:32.000
and the financial services industry.
在金融服务行业。

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:36.000
Or, I've been with the company for two years now.
或者，我在这家公司已经工作两年了。

00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:40.000
Most recently, I was part of the team who worked on campaign ABC,
最近，我参与了ABC项目的团队

00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:42.000
which brought us client X.
为我们带来了客户X。

00:02:42.000 --> 00:02:46.000
So the key thing here is to keep it brief and irrelevant.
这里的关键是保持简短和相关。

00:02:46.000 --> 00:02:50.000
Now is not the time to be telling your whole life story
现在不是讲述你整个人生故事的时候

00:02:50.000 --> 00:02:55.000
or giving a summary of your whole CD and resume or your career history.
也不是概括你整份简历或职业经历的时候。

00:02:55.000 --> 00:02:58.000
And step three, the future.
第三步，未来。

00:02:58.000 --> 00:03:01.000
Here you want to end your introduction on a positive note
在这里，你要以积极的语气结束你的自我介绍

00:03:01.000 --> 00:03:04.000
and show some enthusiasm for the topic at hand.
并对当前话题表现出一些热情。

00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:07.000
Communicate some good energy and show the people in the room
传达一些正能量，让房间里的人知道

00:03:07.000 --> 00:03:10.000
that you're happy to be there and you're happy to be involved.
你很高兴能来到这里并参与其中。

00:03:10.000 --> 00:03:11.000
And it can be simple.
这可以很简单。

00:03:11.000 --> 00:03:13.000
For example, you could just say,
比如，你可以直接说

00:03:13.000 --> 00:03:15.000
it's a pleasure to be here with you all today.
今天很高兴能和大家在一起。

00:03:15.000 --> 00:03:17.000
I'm looking very forward to working with you.
我非常期待与你们共事。

00:03:17.000 --> 00:03:19.000
Or more informally,
或者更随意一些

00:03:19.000 --> 00:03:21.000
I'm excited to be part of this project.
我很兴奋能参与这个项目。

00:03:21.000 --> 00:03:24.000
I think it'll be a great opportunity for all of us.
我认为这对我们所有人来说都是一个很好的机会。

00:03:24.000 --> 00:03:27.000
Alright, now if you put all three of these steps together,
好的，现在如果你把这三步结合起来

00:03:27.000 --> 00:03:31.000
here's an example of how a full introduction might sound.
这是一个完整自我介绍可能听起来的样子。

00:03:31.000 --> 00:03:32.000
Hi, everyone.
大家好。

00:03:32.000 --> 00:03:33.000
I'm Maria Shearan.
我是Maria Shearan。

00:03:33.000 --> 00:03:36.000
I'm a marketing manager at ABC Company,
我是ABC公司的市场经理

00:03:36.000 --> 00:03:40.000
where I'm responsible for lead generation campaigns for North America.
负责北美的潜在客户开发活动。

00:03:41.000 --> 00:03:43.000
I've been with a company for five years now.
我在这家公司已经五年了。

00:03:43.000 --> 00:03:46.000
Prior to that, I managed the social media efforts
在此之前，我管理了社交媒体工作

00:03:46.000 --> 00:03:48.000
for company XYZ.
为XYZ公司。

00:03:48.000 --> 00:03:50.000
It's a pleasure to be here today
今天很高兴来到这里

00:03:50.000 --> 00:03:53.000
and I'm really looking forward to working with you all in this project.
我真的很期待与大家一起参与这个项目。

00:03:53.000 --> 00:03:57.000
So just remember, present past future.
所以只要记住，现在、过去、未来。

00:03:57.000 --> 00:03:58.000
Pretty easy, right?
很简单，对吧？

00:03:58.000 --> 00:04:00.000
But don't stop there.
但不要止步于此。

00:04:00.000 --> 00:04:03.000
Keep practicing your English-speaking skills
继续练习你的英语口语技能

00:04:03.000 --> 00:04:05.000
that you get more and more comfortable speaking
让你越来越自如地使用英语

00:04:05.000 --> 00:04:08.000
and English in these kinds of work situations.
在这种工作场合中。

00:04:08.000 --> 00:04:11.000
And you can do that with this video right here.
你可以通过这里的这个视频来做到。

00:04:11.000 --> 00:04:14.000
Thank you so much for watching and I'll see you there next.
非常感谢收看，我们下次再见。
